<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544477>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 25. Nephochaetopteryx pallidiventris Townsend, 1934, male terminalia. Specimen from Bragança, Pará, Brazil (MPEG).A. Cerci, dorsal view (setation omitted on the right side). B. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. C. Pregonite, left lateral view. D. Postgonite, left lateral view. E. Sternite 5, ventral view (setation omitted on the right side). F. Phallus, left lateral view; arrow showing median rounded projection of vesica. Abbreviations: bp = basiphallus; dp = distiphallus; ip = inner process of vesica; ls = lateral stylus; ms = median stylus; ve = vesica. Scale bars: A, B, E = 0.1 mm; C, D, F = 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4544477/files/figure.png" .

